Sentencas: Energy efficiency of a single solid-oxide fuel cell (SOFC) has been studied in various experimental conditions and directly correlated to the character of the cell.
Titulo: Energy efficiency of a microtubular solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A microtubular cell, which has the exact geometry for stack/module application, is used for this study.
Titulo: Energy efficiency of a microtubular solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The energy efficiency simply improves by increasing the operating temperature, and reaches over 40% (lower heating value: LHV) at the operating temperature of over 700 degrees C in flowing 20% H-2-Ar fuel inside the tube.
Titulo: Energy efficiency of a microtubular solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Impedance analysis has shown that the gas transport is the limiting factor for improving the energy efficiency at lower operating temperatures.
Titulo: Energy efficiency of a microtubular solid-oxide fuel cell
